def multiplication_table(n):
    table = []
    for i in range(1, n + 1):
        row = []
        for j in range(1, n + 1):
            product = i * j
            row.append(product)
        table.append(row)
    return table
For each row i, I compute the product of i and j for every j in range, store it in a variable first, then append it to the row before moving to the next i.
